## Rewrite Checklist

Before finalizing any documentation page, verify:

- [ ] First sentence defines what this is in plain English
- [ ] Prerequisites are listed explicitly at the top
- [ ] Quickstart appears before deep-dive content
- [ ] Every concept has a working code example
- [ ] Code examples are complete and runnable (not pseudocode)
- [ ] Code is provided in at least 3 languages for API operations
- [ ] Every parameter is documented with type, required/optional, and limits
- [ ] All error codes are documented with causes and fixes
- [ ] "What is X?" explanations exist for non-trivial concepts
- [ ] No marketing language ("powerful", "easy", "seamless")
- [ ] No filler phrases ("simply", "just", "obviously")
- [ ] Testing section covers failure scenarios, not just happy path
- [ ] Page ends with next steps or related resources
- [ ] Deprecated features include sunset dates and migration paths
- [ ] Callout blocks are used sparingly and consistently

