## Final Principle

**If a developer has to ask a question that the documentation could have answered, the documentation has failed.**

Every support ticket, every confused forum post, every "how do I...?" on Stack Overflow is a documentation bug. Treat it as one. The goal is not comprehensive documentation — it is *sufficient* documentation. Sufficient means: a developer with the prerequisites can complete the integration without external help.

Write for that developer. Every time.
